---
import Layout from '../layouts/layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Dylan Purbrick | Professional Reflection" activeTab="uni">
  <div class="max-w-4xl">
    <header class="mb-20 border-b border-slate-200 pb-12">
        <h1 class="text-6xl font-black uppercase tracking-tighter mb-4">Professional Reflection</h1>
        <p class="text-brand-purple font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.4em]">Internship Evaluation & Career Trajectory</p>
    </header>

    <div class="space-y-24">
        <section>
            <h2 class="text-brand-orange font-black uppercase text-xs tracking-[0.3em] mb-12">Expectations vs. Reality</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 font-neue text-slate-700">
                <div class="space-y-4">
                    <h3 class="text-[10px] font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-slate-400">Initial Expectations</h3>
                    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed italic border-l-2 border-slate-200 pl-6">
                        "I suppose I expected the work to include elements of hands-on experience, the other workers to be friendly, and that this would be a great opportunity to expand my knowledge to further my career"[cite: 5].
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="space-y-4">
                    <h3 class="text-[10px] font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-slate-400">The Reality</h3>
                    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
                        It didn’t differ much from my expectations, although there was more paperwork than initially anticipated[cite: 7]. The environment was more welcoming and less daunting than expected, with a high degree of friendliness among colleagues[cite: 8].
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="bg-white/50 p-12 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200">
            <h2 class="text-brand-orange font-black uppercase text-xs tracking-[0.3em] mb-12">Core Industrial Lessons</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-16">
                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-black uppercase mb-4">Adaptability & Management</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
                        The ability to be open to change and adaptable are vital; when projects derail or go off-track, an engineer must manage the situation effectively[cite: 10, 11].
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-black uppercase mb-4">Effective Communication</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
                        Clear communication—or "being talkative"—prevents misunderstandings and project derailment, leading to better team relationships and a more comfortable working environment[cite: 12, 13].
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2 class="text-brand-orange font-black uppercase text-xs tracking-[0.3em] mb-12">Value Proposition</h2>
            <p class="text-2xl font-black uppercase text-slate-800 mb-12 leading-tight">
                "A versatile, process-oriented technical resource capable of quickly learning new systems and translating complex engineering knowledge into clear, accessible documentation"[cite: 16].
            </p>
            <div class="space-y-6 font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest text-slate-500">
                <p>• Process Improvement: Reformatting customer records into traceability tables[cite: 17, 18].</p>
                <p>• Systems Analysis: Participating in Autodesk Vault Pro rollout discussions[cite: 19].</p>
                <p>• Technical Communication: Writing manuals for Schenck Balancing and centrifuge stripping[cite: 20, 21].</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2 class="text-brand-orange font-black uppercase text-xs tracking-[0.3em] mb-12">Career Influence & Trajectory</h2>
            <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-12">
                This internship confirmed my foundational interest in hands-on mechanical design and technical execution while revealing a strength in engineering process management[cite: 23]. 
            </p>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 text-xs text-slate-500">
                <ul class="space-y-2 border-t pt-8">
                    <li class="font-black text-industrial-black mb-4">Technical Exposure</li>
                    <li>• CAD: 1038 Press Shaft Bullnose [cite: 28]</li>
                    <li>• Workshop: Tallow centrifuge stripping [cite: 29]</li>
                    <li>• Testing: Gearboxes and bearings [cite: 29]</li>
                </ul>
                <ul class="space-y-2 border-t pt-8">
                    <li class="font-black text-industrial-black mb-4">Process Ownership</li>
                    <li>• Manuals: Balancing machine user guides [cite: 32]</li>
                    <li>• Templates: Evaluation reports for customers [cite: 33]</li>
                    <li>• Project Oversight: 1800 Cooker Wear Sleeves [cite: 30]</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="border-t-4 border-industrial-black pt-24">
            <h2 class="text-brand-purple font-black uppercase text-xs tracking-[0.3em] mb-12">Internal Audit & Peer Feedback</h2>
            <div class="bg-white/50 p-12 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200">
                <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 leading-relaxed italic mb-12">
                    "Reflecting on my collaboration with Olivia, Muhaimin, and Eric, our team focused on the mechanical structure of a mechatronic system. Key takeaways included the importance of bridging the gap between technical CAD modeling and cost-effective material procurement."
                </p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="font-black uppercase text-[10px] tracking-widest mb-4">Technical Integration</h4>
                        <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 leading-relaxed">Bringing industry-standard QA practices to student projects, specifically in BOM verification.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="font-black uppercase text-[10px] tracking-widest mb-4">Leadership Insight</h4>
                        <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 leading-relaxed">Utilizing supervisor-level management skills to maintain project milestones under pressure.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
